                            <comment id="14171116" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 14 Oct 2014 16:13:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1631810 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kwall&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kwall&quot;&gt;kwall&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;qpid/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1631810&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1631810&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-6152&quot; title=&quot;Connection close timeout too short when connections have many sessions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;QPID-6152&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;QPID-6152&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Java Client&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Allow connection/session close time to be overridden by system property.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Change implementation so that the timeout is applied individually to each session close, the connection and&lt;br/&gt;
the shutdown of the task pool.   Also moved the shutdown of the task pool to a finally, so that it occurs&lt;br/&gt;
even if one or more sessions fail to close.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
